title: For Sale:  SC CONCEALED WEAPONS CLASS, AUG, 2, 2014, 10 slots left.
postcontent:
SC Concealed Weapons Permit Course, Saturday August 2nd 2014, from 9am to 3pm hosted by Blue Ridge Shooting Sports at 1310 W Wade Hampton Blvd, Greer, SC, 29651. Course cost $50. You need to bring your firearm, 50 rounds of ammo, and a belt with holster. Any questions feel free to call me at REDACTED or go to Facebook and add Blue Ridge Firearms Training. SEE BELOW COMMENTS FOR MORE INFO.

Course Requirements

#1. Absolutely no charges/convictions for any Felonies, Criminal Domestic Violence, Drugs, or any misdemeanors that carry more than 2+ years imprisonment / probation or any charge that would prohibit you from owning or possessing a firearm. If found NOT GUILTY you should still be eligible. If you
are unsure about your status you can contact SLED at REDACTED for clarification.

#2. All necessary paperwork will be provided by me. Make sure that the address on your SC drivers license matches your current address. If not SLED will send the application back.

#3. Wear a tight neck shirt, no collared shirts please. Also bring a ball cap guys and girls. All other protective gear (safety glasses and hearing protection) will be provided by me. If you want to bring your own protective gear that is fine as well.

#4. Have a holster with at least 1 level of retention. This means a type of holster with a strap, snap, or button that secures the handgun from being pulled from the holster without being unsecured first. Wear long pants with a belt please. 

#5. Bring a small to medium caliber handgun with 50 rounds of ammunition, .22 cal, .32cal, .380cal, .38cal, 9mm, .40cal, 10mm, .45cal. No magnum high caliber pistols please. If you do not currently own a firearm, speak with me prior to the class and arrangements can be made to borrow one. You will still be responsible for the ammo for the borrowed firearm.

#6. The total cost of the course is $100. This needs to be separated as such, $50. cash/card for the instructor, and a $50. cashiers check or money order made out to SLED. You DO NOT have to have the SLED fee the day of the class, only when you get ready to mail the application off.

Most important is safety, Know your firearm prior to class, if you need to practice to familiarize yourself with your firearm or to schedule a class, call me at REDACTED.
